<p>&nbsp;</p>";s:7:"summary";s:86:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break inbetween recording.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>";}i:139;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4779";s:4:"link";s:71:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-november-10-1967";s:5:"title";s:49:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: November 10, 1967";s:11:"description";s:1116:"<h1 class="title single-title entry-title"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Filming: Hello, Goodbye</span></h1>
<p>The Beatles filmed promotional footage for their forthcoming single <em><strong>Hello, Goodbye</strong></em> at London's Saville Theatre on this day.</p>
<p>Without an audience present, they mimed to the song on stage. At the time the theatre was still leased by NEMS Enterprises, despite the recent death of Brian Epstein.</p>
<p>Paul McCartney was the director of the three promo clips made, using different costumes for each. For the first The Beatles wore their Sgt Pepper uniforms before a psychedelic backdrop. The clip also had cutaways of the group waving to the camera in their 1963 collarless suits, and some dancing girls wearing Hawaiian costumes in the finale.</p>
<p>The second clip had The Beatles in their normal (for 1967, at least) clothes, with the dancing girls again appearing in the finale. The third was made of outtakes from the first two clips, plus footage of The Beatles dancing the Twist.</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/nov10.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>";s:7:"summary";s:1116:"<h1 class="title single-title entry-title"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Filming: Hello, Goodbye</span></h1>
<p>The Beatles filmed promotional footage for their forthcoming single <em><strong>Hello, Goodbye</strong></em> at London's Saville Theatre on this day.</p>
<p>Without an audience present, they mimed to the song on stage. At the time the theatre was still leased by NEMS Enterprises, despite the recent death of Brian Epstein.</p>
<p>Paul McCartney was the director of the three promo clips made, using different costumes for each. For the first The Beatles wore their Sgt Pepper uniforms before a psychedelic backdrop. The clip also had cutaways of the group waving to the camera in their 1963 collarless suits, and some dancing girls wearing Hawaiian costumes in the finale.</p>
<p>The second clip had The Beatles in their normal (for 1967, at least) clothes, with the dancing girls again appearing in the finale. The third was made of outtakes from the first two clips, plus footage of The Beatles dancing the Twist.</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/nov10.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>";}i:140;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4778";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-november-9-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: November 9, 1967";s:11:"description";s:510:"<p>John Lennon poses in a still from the film How I Won the War on the cover of the<strong> first</strong> issue of Rolling Stone. Lennon would go on to grace the cover two more times within the first ten issues on his way to becoming one of the most featured people on the cover of Rolling Stone.</p>
