<p>&nbsp;</p>";}i:152;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4766";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-28-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 28, 1967";s:11:"description";s:38:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:38:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break.</p>";}i:153;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4765";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-27-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 27, 1967";s:11:"description";s:38:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:38:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break.</p>";}i:154;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4764";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-26-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 26, 1967";s:11:"description";s:45:"<p>The Beatles are in-between recordings.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:45:"<p>The Beatles are in-between recordings.</p>";}i:155;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4763";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-25-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 25, 1967";s:11:"description";s:424:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studio, London</p>
<p>A 7:00 pm to 3:00 am session in which "The Fool On The Hill", now complete, was mixed into mono and edited. And then Paul overdubbed bass onto simultaneous reduction mixdowns of "Hello, Goodbye" - the best being "Take 21".</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Source: The Complete Beatles Chronicle - M. Lewishon</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Oct25.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>";s:7:"summary";s:424:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studio, London</p>
<p>A 7:00 pm to 3:00 am session in which "The Fool On The Hill", now complete, was mixed into mono and edited. And then Paul overdubbed bass onto simultaneous reduction mixdowns of "Hello, Goodbye" - the best being "Take 21".</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Source: The Complete Beatles Chronicle - M. Lewishon</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Oct25.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>";}i:156;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4762";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-24-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 24, 1967";s:11:"description";s:57:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break between recordings.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:57:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break between recordings.</p>";}i:157;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4761";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-23-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 23, 1967";s:11:"description";s:40:"<p>The Beatles taking a break today.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:40:"<p>The Beatles taking a break today.</p>";}i:158;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4760";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-22-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 22, 1967";s:11:"description";s:44:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break today.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:44:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break today.</p>";}i:159;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4759";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-21-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 21, 1967";s:11:"description";s:44:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break today.</p>";s:7:"summary";s:44:"<p>The Beatles are taking a break today.</p>";}i:160;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4758";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-20-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 20, 1967";s:11:"description";s:1451:"<h1 class="title single-title entry-title"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Recording: The Fool On The Hill, Hello, Goodbye</span></h1>
<p>Studio Three, EMI Studios, Abbey Road<br />Producer: George Martin<br />Engineer: Ken Scott</p>
<p>This session was booked for the overdubbing of flutes and violas onto The Fool On The Hill and Hello, Goodbye.</p>
<p>It took place between 7pm and 3.45am, and began with the overdubbing of flutes to The Fool On The Hill. The flautists were Jack Ellory and brothers Christopher and Richard Taylor.</p>
<p>The flute parts were recorded on a separate tape as take seven, as all tracks on the main tape were full. On October 25, 1967 takes six and seven were mixed in sync to create a final mono master.</p>
<p>Hello, Goodbye still had its working title Hello Hello at this stage. Viola players Ken Essex and Birnbaum had been booked to play between 8pm and 11pm, but the session overran and they were paid a double fee.</p>
<p>Paul McCartney was doodling at the piano and George Martin was sitting next to him writing down what Paul was playing.</p>
<p>Leo Birnbaum<br />The Complete Beatles Recording Sessions, Mark Lewisohn</p>
<p>Also during this session, Paul McCartney wiped the guitar solo and replaced it with the line "Why why why why why why do you say goodbye, goodbye?", which was treated with heavy echo.</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Oct20.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>
