<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Oct14.png" alt="" width="100" /></p>";}i:167;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4751";s:4:"link";s:70:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-october-13-1967";s:5:"title";s:48:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: October 13, 1967";s:11:"description";s:381:"<p>The Sgt. Pepper album was widely perceived by listeners as the soundtrack to the Summer of Love, occupying the number one position of the Billboard Top LPs in the US for 15 weeks, from July 1st to October 13, 1967. Its initial commercial success exceeded that of all previous Beatles albums.</p>
