<div class="source"><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Sept27.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></div>";}i:184;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4734";s:4:"link";s:72:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-september-26-1967";s:5:"title";s:50:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: September 26, 1967";s:11:"description";s:487:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studios, London</p>
<p>A re-make of "The Fool On The Hill", with a basic rock recordig numbered take five, onto which a host of instrumentswere overdubbed. This was then reduced into take six with vocals and ass superimposed.</p>
<p>Producer George Martin was absent for this 7:00 pm to 4:15 am session, the Beatles' new balance engineer Ken Scott having to fulfill double duties.</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Sept26.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></p>";s:7:"summary";s:487:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studios, London</p>
<p>A re-make of "The Fool On The Hill", with a basic rock recordig numbered take five, onto which a host of instrumentswere overdubbed. This was then reduced into take six with vocals and ass superimposed.</p>
