<p>&nbsp;</p>";}i:220;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4698";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-august-21-1967";s:5:"title";s:47:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: August 21, 1967";s:11:"description";s:42:"<p>The Beatles enjoying a little break</p>";s:7:"summary";s:42:"<p>The Beatles enjoying a little break</p>";}i:221;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4697";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-august-20-1967";s:5:"title";s:47:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: August 20, 1967";s:11:"description";s:372:"<p><span style="color: #555; font-size: 16px;" data-reactid="120">Ringo Starr arrives at Queen Charlotte&rsquo;s Hospital in London August 20, 1967, to visit his wife Maureen and their newly born, second son.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #555; font-size: 16px;" data-reactid="120"><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Aug20.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></span></p>";s:7:"summary";s:372:"<p><span style="color: #555; font-size: 16px;" data-reactid="120">Ringo Starr arrives at Queen Charlotte&rsquo;s Hospital in London August 20, 1967, to visit his wife Maureen and their newly born, second son.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #555; font-size: 16px;" data-reactid="120"><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Aug20.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></span></p>";}i:222;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4696";s:4:"link";s:69:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-august-19-1967";s:5:"title";s:47:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: August 19, 1967";s:11:"description";s:1435:"<h1 class="title single-title entry-title"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Jason Starkey is born</span></h1>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Ringo Starr and Maureen Starkey's second son, Jason, was born on 19 August 1967. He was the third Beatles baby after Julian Lennon and Zak Starkey.</span></p>
<p>L<span style="font-size: 10pt;">ike his elder brother, Jason was born in Queen Charlotte's Hospital in Hammersmith, London. His name was chosen by his mother.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">In later years Jason worked in the music industry, becoming a road manager and drummer. He once described his famous family as a burden, saying: "Being Ringo Starr's son is the biggest drag of my life. It's a total pain."</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">In 1987 Jason Starkey was fined &pound;125 after being caught stealing a car stereo, and two years later appeared twice in court on drugs charges. He played in a succession of bands including Buddy Curtis and the Grasshoppers, The People's Friend, Empire Of Sponge, and with his brother Zak, Musty Jack Sponge and the Exploding Nudists.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Despite his earlier problems with drugs and the law, Jason settled down in England with his wife Flora and two sons Louie and Sonny.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/17_blog/Aug19.jpg" alt="" width="100" /></span></p>
