<p>&nbsp;</p>";}i:363;a:5:{s:4:"guid";s:9:"Blog:4554";s:4:"link";s:68:"http://beatlesradio.com/the-beatles-50-years-ago-today-march-31-1967";s:5:"title";s:46:"The Beatles 50 Years Ago Today: March 31, 1967";s:11:"description";s:368:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studios, in London</p>
<p>"With A Little Help From My Friend" and "Being For The Benefit of Mr. Kite!" were mixed into mono during this 7:00 pm - 3:00 am session, the latter only after overdubbing of another organ part and a glockenspiel.</p>
<p><img src="/Content/Images/uploaded/_50th-blog/50th blog/50 blog/March 31.jpg" alt="" width="300" /></p>";s:7:"summary";s:368:"<p>Studio Two, EMI Studios, in London</p>
